## Understanding High-Yield Savings Accounts

High-yield savings accounts (HYSAs) offer interest rates many times higher than traditional bank savings accounts. While the national average savings rate is just 0.40%, the best online savings accounts offer APYs ranging from 3.40% to 5.00%.

### Why Online Banks Offer Better Rates

Online banks can offer significantly higher interest rates because they have lower overhead costs—no physical branches to maintain, fewer staff, and reduced real estate expenses. These savings are passed directly to customers through higher APYs.

## How Much Can You Earn?

The difference between a traditional savings account and a high-yield account is substantial:

| Deposit Amount | Traditional (0.40% APY) | High-Yield (4.00% APY) | Difference |
|----------------|-------------------------|------------------------|------------|
